olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 packet brown rice
3 cup water
2 radish
1 white turnip
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet beef strips
1 tsp honey
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, add brown rice and the water and bring to the boil.
• Reduce heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, until rice is soft,
25-30 minutes. Drain the rice and set aside.
• Return pan to medium heat, then add a dash of olive oil. Cook garlic until
fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Return rice to the pan, then add a pinch of salt and stir to combine. Remove
from heat.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish. Finely chop white turnip. Roughly chop baby
spinach leaves.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips, Tex-Mex spice blend, a pinch of
salt and a drizzle of olive oil.

• When the rice has 5 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan
over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and
cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add the honey and mild chipotle sauce and
gently toss to combine. Season to taste.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• While the beef is cooking, combine radish, turnip, baby spinach and a drizzle
of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a second medium bowl. Season to
taste.
• Divide garlic brown rice between bowls. Top with Tex-Mex beef and radish
salsa.
• Serve with Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!